    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect criticality flags in E-RAB Modification Indication\n\n### Summary\nThe `s1ap_eNB_generate_E_RAB_Modification_Indication` function was using incorrect criticality flags for mandatory IEs (MME_UE_S1AP_ID and eNB_UE_S1AP_ID), causing the MME to reject valid E-RAB modification indications. This led to failed bearer modification procedures and radio link failures when UEs attempted to modify their bearers.\n\nThe issue was that these IEs were marked with `S1AP_Criticality_reject` instead of `S1AP_Criticality_ignore`, which is inconsistent with other similar S1AP procedures and can cause interoperability issues with certain MME implementations that strictly enforce criticality handling.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure a UE to trigger an E-RAB modification procedure (e.g., through QoS changes)\n2. Observe that the gNB sends an E-RAB Modification Indication with incorrect criticality flags\n3. Some MME implementations will reject the message due to the incorrect flags\n4. The bearer modification fails and may lead to radio link failure\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/S1AP/s1ap_eNB_nas_procedures.c`: Changed criticality values for MME_UE_S1AP_ID and eNB_UE_S1AP_ID IEs from `S1AP_Criticality_reject` to `S1AP_Criticality_ignore` in the `s1ap_eNB_generate_E_RAB_Modification_Indication` function to align with other S1AP procedures\n"
}